-- Cordova installation

1. npm install -g cordova
2. go to a existing angularjs project (cd path/to/project)
3. cordova create cordova --link-to=project/app or dist folder  #KEY ARGUMENT --link-to
4. cordova platform add android
5. cordova build android
6. cordova run android
7. make sure debuggins is enabled on the device.
8. When working in the CLI you can define app icon(s) via <icon> element (config.xml). If you do not specify an icon then the Apache Cordova logo is used.
8. <icon src="res/ios/icon.png" platform="ios" width="57" height="57" density="mdpi" />
9. The above will replace the default cordova/phonegap icon to the icon you provide.
10. Make sure you point to the dist folder to make sure everything's working fine.
